9#ifndef EAPOL_AUTH_SM_H
10#define EAPOL_AUTH_SM_H
11
12#define EAPOL_SM_PREAUTH BIT(0)
13#define EAPOL_SM_WAIT_START BIT(1)
14#define EAPOL_SM_USES_WPA BIT(2)
15#define EAPOL_SM_FROM_PMKSA_CACHE BIT(3)
16
17struct eapol_auth_config {
18 int eap_reauth_period;
19 int wpa;
20 int individual_wep_key_len;
21 int eap_server;
22 void *ssl_ctx;
23 void *msg_ctx;
24 void *eap_sim_db_priv;
25 char *eap_req_id_text; /* a copy of this will be allocated */
26 size_t eap_req_id_text_len;
27 int erp_send_reauth_start;
28 char *erp_domain; /* a copy of this will be allocated */
29 int erp; /* Whether ERP is enabled on authentication server */
30 unsigned int tls_session_lifetime;
31 unsigned int tls_flags;
32 u8 *pac_opaque_encr_key;
33 u8 *eap_fast_a_id;
34 size_t eap_fast_a_id_len;
35 char *eap_fast_a_id_info;
36 int eap_fast_prov;
37 int pac_key_lifetime;
38 int pac_key_refresh_time;
39 int eap_sim_aka_result_ind;
40 int tnc;
41 struct wps_context *wps;
42 int fragment_size;
43 u16 pwd_group;
44 int pbc_in_m1;
45 const u8 *server_id;
46 size_t server_id_len;
47
48 /* Opaque context pointer to owner data for callback functions */
49 void *ctx;
50};
51
52struct eap_user;
53struct eap_server_erp_key;
54
55typedef enum {
56 EAPOL_LOGGER_DEBUG, EAPOL_LOGGER_INFO, EAPOL_LOGGER_WARNING
57} eapol_logger_level;
58
59enum eapol_event {
60 EAPOL_AUTH_SM_CHANGE,
61 EAPOL_AUTH_REAUTHENTICATE
62};
63
64struct eapol_auth_cb {
65 void (*eapol_send)(void *ctx, void *sta_ctx, u8 type, const u8 *data,
66 size_t datalen);
67 void (*aaa_send)(void *ctx, void *sta_ctx, const u8 *data,
68 size_t datalen);
69 void (*finished)(void *ctx, void *sta_ctx, int success, int preauth,
70 int remediation);
71 int (*get_eap_user)(void *ctx, const u8 *identity, size_t identity_len,
72 int phase2, struct eap_user *user);
73 int (*sta_entry_alive)(void *ctx, const u8 *addr);
74 void (*logger)(void *ctx, const u8 *addr, eapol_logger_level level,
75 const char *txt);
76 void (*set_port_authorized)(void *ctx, void *sta_ctx, int authorized);
77 void (*abort_auth)(void *ctx, void *sta_ctx);
78 void (*tx_key)(void *ctx, void *sta_ctx);
79 void (*eapol_event)(void *ctx, void *sta_ctx, enum eapol_event type);
80 struct eap_server_erp_key * (*erp_get_key)(void *ctx,
81 const char *keyname);
82 int (*erp_add_key)(void *ctx, struct eap_server_erp_key *erp);
83};
84
85
86struct eapol_authenticator * eapol_auth_init(struct eapol_auth_config *conf,
87 struct eapol_auth_cb *cb);
88void eapol_auth_deinit(struct eapol_authenticator *eapol);
89struct eapol_state_machine *
90eapol_auth_alloc(struct eapol_authenticator *eapol, const u8 *addr,
91 int flags, const struct wpabuf *assoc_wps_ie,
92 const struct wpabuf *assoc_p2p_ie, void *sta_ctx,
93 const char *identity, const char *radius_cui);
94void eapol_auth_free(struct eapol_state_machine *sm);
95void eapol_auth_step(struct eapol_state_machine *sm);
96int eapol_auth_dump_state(struct eapol_state_machine *sm, char *buf,
97 size_t buflen);
98int eapol_auth_eap_pending_cb(struct eapol_state_machine *sm, void *ctx);
99void eapol_auth_reauthenticate(struct eapol_state_machine *sm);
100int eapol_auth_set_conf(struct eapol_state_machine *sm, const char *param,
101 const char *value);
102
103#endif /* EAPOL_AUTH_SM_H */
